│ 32-bit value, can be negative, but the 64-bit abs preserves the large       │
│ positive value.                                                             │
│                                                                             │
│ The fundamental problem is that `trunc(abs(x)) != abs(trunc(x))` when x is  │
│ a large positive number that appears negative when truncated.               │
│                                                                             │
│ Therefore, the SLP vectorizer should not vectorize patterns where an abs    │
│ intrinsic is followed by truncation to a smaller type, because this         │
